            <h3><p align="center" style="color: black"><b>Dress Code For Monarch College Students</b><p></h3>
            <h4><p style="color: #002a80">School uniforms make an essential contribution to the development of community spirit and pride that all students feel by being part of the Monarch College. </p></h4>
                            <img src="images/A11.jpg"width ="400px" height ="400px">

            <h2><b>Skirts</b></h2>
                            Girls skirt must be at least knee length.

                            <h2><b>Trousers</b></h2>
                            Boys trousers must be worn on the waist,not the hip.<br><br>
                            The belt should be plain black with a silver buckel.


                            <h2><b>Blouses</b></h2>
                            Girls blouses with a tailored bottom edge may be worn outside of skirts.<br><br>
                            Top buttons must be fastened at all times.
                            <br>
                            <br><br><br><br>
                            <h2><b>Shirts</b></h2>
                            Boys shirts must be tucked securely into trousers at all times.<br><br>
                            Top buttons must be fastened at all time.<br><br>
                            Long-sleeved shirts must be buttoned at the cuff.

                            <h2><b>Ties</b></h2>
                            The knot should be a standard size- neither too tight nor too large.<br><br>
                            The knot should cover the top bottom of the shirt or blouse.

                            <h2><b>Shoes</b></h2>
                            School shoes should have black leather uppers.<br><br>
                            The sides of the soles should also be black.<br><br>
                            The shoe must have a formal,businesslike style.<br><br>
                            The shoes must not have sports-style soles or titching.<br><br>
                            The heel should be very low.Platform soles are not permitted.<br><br>
                            Shoes should be kept well pplished.



                            <h2><b>Blazer</b></h2>
                            Blazer collar must be turned up.<br><br>
                            Blazer sleeves must not be rolled or folded up.

                            <h2><b>Hair</b></h2>
                            Students hair may not be shorter than 9 millimetres.<br><br>
                            Boys may not have facial hair,except that they may wear a neatly trimmed moustache.<br><br>
                            Students may not dye or highlight their hair in any way.<br><br>
                            Students may not use products such as hair gel, wax, mousse, cream or oil.







